  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Over the past 5 years, there has been a change in clinical practice with the use of cuffed
      instead of uncuffed endotracheal tubes in infants and children. Two manufacturing companies
      have recently introduced syringe-like devices to the market which allow the measurement of
      the intracuff pressure. This study proposes to prospectively compare the intracuff pressure
      from these devices with the gold standard technique (manometer).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
